Sandford Drexel  Smith: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 23, 2017 10:17 AM ET
Healthcare Equipment and Supplies

Company Overview of Sanofi Biosurgery Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Sandford Drexel  Smith  Executive Vice President and President of International Group, Sanofi Biosurgery Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 11 different industries.See Board Relationships70--
Background

		Mr. Sandford Drexel Smith, also known as Sandy, BS, serves as an Executive Vice President at Sanofi Biosurgery Inc. Mr. Smith served as the Interim Chief Executive Officer of Aegerion Pharmaceuticals, Inc. from July 2015 to January 7, 2016. He served as President of Genzyme International Group since January 2000. He served as a Corporate Vice President and President of Genzyme Europe. In his 15 years at Genzyme, he was responsible for the successful global launch of ... 12 new products in various therapeutic categories, including rare diseases. He joined Genzyme in 1996 and served as a Vice President and General Manager of Genzyme International and President of Genzyme Specialty Therapeutics. Following Sanofi's acquisition of Genzyme in April of 2011, he was responsible for the integration of Genzyme's international business into the Sanofiglobal organization. From January 1998 to January 2000, he served as the President of Genzyme General's Therapeutics business unit. He served as a Senior Vice President of Genzyme Biosurgery Corporation since January 2003. He served as President of International Group and Executive Vice President at Genzyme Oncology, Inc. since January 2000 and June 2006 respectively. He served as the President at Therapeutics International, Genzyme Corporation from October 1997 to December 2000 and served as a Vice President and General Manager, Specialty Therapeutics and International Group from April 1996 to February 1997, Genzyme Corporation from May 1996 to September 1996. He served as the President and Chief Executive Officer at Repligen Corporation from 1986 to March 1996. He served as Senior Vice President of Sanofi Biosurgery Inc. until January 2003. He served as Executive Vice President of Genzyme Corporation. He served a number of positions at Bristol-Myers Squibb Company throughout Asia and Japan from 1977 to 1986, including, Vice President of Corporate Development and Planning at the United States Pharmaceutical and Nutritional Group. For the past 20 years, he has focused on drugs and therapies for rare genetic diseases. Since December 2011, he was Founder and Chairman of Global Biolink Partners. He served as the Chairman of Aegerion Pharmaceuticals, Inc. from January 7, 2016 to November 29, 2016 and its Director until November 29, 2016. He served as Vice Chairman at Novelion Therapeutics Inc until March 30, 2017. He served as Vice Chairman of Ariad Pharmaceuticals Inc from January 1999 to November 3, 2008. he served as Managing Director at Tullis Health Investors Inc. since January 04, 2012. He served as Chairman of Advisory Board of Tullis Health Investors Inc. He has been Advisory Board Member of Tullis Health Investors Inc. since 2008. He has been an Independent Director at Neuralstem, Inc. since March 2014. He has been Director of Apricus Biosciences, Inc. since August 11, 2014 and Cytokinetics, Incorporated since March 2012. He has been Independent Director at Akcea Therapeutics, Inc. since March 15, 2017. He served as a Director of ARIAD Pharmaceuticals, Inc from October 1991 to December 1, 2008. He served as a Director at Novelion Therapeutics Inc since November 29, 2016 until March 30, 2017. He served as a Director of CSP Inc. from 1993 to March 31, 2003, Repligen Corporation from 1986 to March 1996 and Nventa Biopharmaceuticals Corporation from May 2007 to 2009. He served as a Director of BioBehavioral Diagnostics Company. He has more than 30 years of experience in global biotech and pharmaceutical executive leadership, with a particular strength in establishing and growing commercial platforms. He has over 30 years of commercial, general management and corporate development experience in the global biotech, biopharmaceutical and pharmaceutical executive leadership industries. Mr. Smith holds a B.Sc. degree in Business from the University of Denver and completed Graduate Studies in Finance at Columbia University.Read Full Background




